14_large_angle_rad


  1. Question

    Which graph shows a \(\frac{-3\pi}{5}\) angle in standard position?



    1. A
    2. B
    3. C
    4. D
    5. E
    6. F
    7. G
    8. H

    Solution

    The given angle is \(\frac{-3\pi}{5}\). The angle is negative, so the angle rotates clockwise.

    Each wedge shown below corresponds to an angle of \(\frac{\pi}{5}\). So, we just need to turn across 3 wedges clockwise.
